'''Stefano Colonna''' was the name of several members of the Italian family of [[Colonna family|Colonna]]. The most important include:
*'''Stefano Colonna the Elder''' (1265 &ndash; c. 1348) was son of [[Giovanni Colonna (died 1293)|Giovanni Colonna]] and one of the most important political figures in Rome in the first half of the 14th century. He was heir of the [[Papal States|Papal]] fief of [[Palestrina]]. In 1290 he was named count of [[Romagna]], and he was several times Senator of [[History of Rome#Medieval Rome|Rome]] and [[Holy Roman Empire|Imperial]] vicar in [[Italy]]. A staunch [[Ghibelline]], he struggled for large part of his life against the Guelph [[Orsini]] family. He was a protector of [[Petrarch]], who dedicated two sonnets and other works to him. He was also a fierce opponent of [[Cola di Rienzo]], leader of the popular rebellion of Rome in 1347. He was brother to [[Sciarra Colonna]]. *'''Stefano Colonna the Younger''' (died 1347), son of the former, was Senator of Rome in 1306 and 1330. He was killed (together with his sons Giovanni and Camillo) at the [[battle of Porta San Lorenzo]] (1347) against the troops of Cola di Rienzo. *'''Stefanello''' (died c. 1368), son of the former, was the first of the Palestrina branch of the family. *'''Stefano Colonna di [[Palestrina]]''' (16th century). Commander of the [[Republic of Florence|Florentine]] militia during the siege of Florence.<ref name=af>{{cite web|title=L'assedio di Firenze:cronologia|url=http://cronologia.leonardo.it/storia/aa1528a.htm|website=cronologia.leonardo.it|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref>
